## Flow Name

## High Level Summary
This integration exposes an HTTP API at `/api/*` and `/console/*` for account management. It routes incoming requests based on API configuration and handles standard HTTP errors (400, 404, 405, 406, 415, 501) with dynamic status codes (defaulting to 200 for success and 500 for errors). The integration follows an API gateway pattern. No external systems or databases are directly involved in this integration.

## Detailed Steps
# Account Management API Integration Summary

- This integration implements an HTTP-based API endpoint for account management functionality
- The API is exposed at two paths:
  - Main API endpoint at `/api/*`
  - Console interface at `/console/*`
- The integration is triggered by incoming HTTP requests to these endpoints
- The implementation routes incoming requests based on an API configuration
- No external systems, databases, or other integration points are visible in the provided code
- Error handling is implemented for standard HTTP error scenarios:
  - 400 (Bad Request)
  - 404 (Not Found)
  - 405 (Method Not Allowed)
  - 406 (Not Acceptable)
  - 415 (Unsupported Media Type)
  - 501 (Not Implemented)
- Response handling includes dynamic status codes with defaults of 200 for success and 500 for errors
- The implementation follows a standard API gateway pattern that would route requests to appropriate handlers



## Error Handling
| Scenario | Error Code | Response Object/Log Message |
|----------|------------|----------------------------|
| Invalid request format or validation failure | APIKIT:BAD_REQUEST | `{"message": "Bad request"}` with HTTP status 400 |
| Resource endpoint not found | APIKIT:NOT_FOUND | `{"message": "Resource not found"}` with HTTP status 404 |
| HTTP method not allowed for the resource | APIKIT:METHOD_NOT_ALLOWED | `{"message": "Method not allowed"}` with HTTP status 405 |
| Requested media type in Accept header not supported | APIKIT:NOT_ACCEPTABLE | `{"message": "Not acceptable"}` with HTTP status 406 |
| Content-Type header specifies unsupported media type | APIKIT:UNSUPPORTED_MEDIA_TYPE | `{"message": "Unsupported media type"}` with HTTP status 415 |
| API endpoint exists but not implemented | APIKIT:NOT_IMPLEMENTED | `{"message": "Not Implemented"}` with HTTP status 501 |

## Security
1. No authentication or authorization mechanisms are implemented for the HTTP listener in the account-management-api-main flow.
2. The HTTP listener is configured to accept connections on all network interfaces (0.0.0.0) on port 8081 without any security measures.
3. No encryption methods are implemented for the API endpoints.
